29/07/2005
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Foreign Minister Miodrag Vlahovic says Montenegro supports a recently signed agreement with NATO, allowing Alliance troops to use Serbia-Montenegro for transit purposes. 
He told the Tanjug news agency on Thursday (28 July) that Podgorica also fully supports the actions of Federal Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic regarding that agreement. 
Serbian-Montenegrin President Svetozar Marovic said on Thursday that he would ensure it is approved by the federal and republican parliaments. 
(Tanjug, RTCG, Mina - 28/07/05)
